    {
      "id": 1,
      "text": "On a winter morning the glistening ice mirrored a magic new island in the midst of the lake soon to be described by national writers as one of the seven most beautiful in the world - Candlewood Isle.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        15
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://candlewoodisle.communitysite.com/p/Isle-History"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "By 1929 a causeway and a sign appeared, and a real estate office sprang up to promote the Isle.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        16
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://candlewoodisle.communitysite.com/p/Isle-History"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The real estate development firm Miller, Price and Schiller acquired all the property north of the causeway.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        17
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://candlewoodisle.communitysite.com/p/Isle-History"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Developers set aside the northern tip for a beach and a tiny clubhouse to form a nucleus for the new community.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        20
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://candlewoodisle.communitysite.com/p/Isle-History"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "The first people to purchase land and build small Adirondack lodges were a mix of clergy, doctors, lawyers, business‑owners and corporate executives.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        21
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://candlewoodisle.communitysite.com/p/Isle-History"
    },
    {
